Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.54,0:00:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school student Shinichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.55,0:00:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although smaller, my mind\Nremains that of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.55,0:00:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's is a ransom case!\NMoney won't buy love!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the evidence is underwater,\Nthere's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century in 100 years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:27.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When told to cry, I laughed instead{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:39.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century\Nin a long, long time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:45.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're leaping into a wide open world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:52.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The things I tried to\Nunderstand as a child{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:58.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}remain a mystery even as an adult{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm neither a hotshot\Nnor especially great{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.89,0:01:11.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I understand is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's neither an answer nor the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:23.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I have faith in is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:28.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That and nothing else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fake Ransom Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time. Don't push it, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.68,0:02:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hostage's safety\Nis the most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.19,0:02:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hardly believe this\Nis Mr. Takei's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.36,0:02:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.07,0:02:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let Naoko go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.62,0:02:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. I'll let you see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper showed up\Nin a mini-van, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.29,0:02:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:02:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.89,0:03:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring the money now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.18,0:03:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. There are policemen hiding here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.77,0:03:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.95,0:03:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.36,0:03:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.44,0:03:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car never braked\Nand flew right into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.32,0:04:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were classmates\Nwith the kidnapped Takei Naoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.50,0:04:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.33,0:04:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takei Naoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.72,0:04:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She always looked so lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.13,0:04:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no way\Nshe could've survived this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.14,0:04:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't find her body\Nat the river bottom either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.23,0:04:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The river runs fast in this area, so\Nshe may have been taken downstream...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.54,0:04:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, her body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left everything up to you because\NI thought I could trust the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you screwed everything up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.66,0:04:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give her back! Give Naoko back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.30,0:05:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the mini-van fell front-first,\Nthen why is only the side window broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hammer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.85,0:05:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan! Not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.85,0:05:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lousy kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can no longer trust the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I would like you to\Ncatch the one responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.03,0:05:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My secretary Hanai-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}will give you the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.11,0:05:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hanai Akiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.76,0:05:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you explain the circumstances\Nunder which she was kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko-{\i1}chan {\i0}and I were\Nsupposed to see a movie that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.55,0:05:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I went to meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But hours passed\Nand she never showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you grew worried\Nand contacted the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.47,0:05:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I realized\Nit was a kidnapping
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.68,0:05:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the kidnapper\Ncalled my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.06,0:06:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper warned you\Nnot to tell the police, I assume?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I immediately told Mr. Takei...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all my fault; if only I hadn't\Nsuggested seeing a movie!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.45,0:06:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any ideas about\Nwho the kidnapper may be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have hired you if I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me put it another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know anyone who\Nmay hold a grudge against you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my rudeness, but you\Nare an infamous corporate raider.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.01,0:06:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you haven't\Nmade a lot of enemies in your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.65,0:06:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man's finally\Ngetting better at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember every single thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.56,0:06:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! Business is war!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The losers are the ones at fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.07,0:06:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.87,0:06:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! He backs down too easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.81,0:06:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room\Nwas on the 2nd floor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? How's Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.70,0:06:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.45,0:06:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko really thought of\NAkiko-{\i1}san {\i0}as an older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.41,0:06:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said that she was also\Nlike a mother to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.67,0:07:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since her real mother\Nhad died when she was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.13,0:07:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.34,0:07:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.76,0:07:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright? We called\Nout to you a couple times...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I damaged my hearing a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? She's--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.27,0:07:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you given up on Naoko-{\i1}chan {\i0}too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's alive! I just know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they've looked this hard\Nand still haven't found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.46,0:07:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's probably--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.59,0:07:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That poor woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.28,0:07:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!\NLet's take a look over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.40,0:08:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody might've seen it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anything out of\Nthe ordinary happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can say that. The police asked\Nus to help with their investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.16,0:08:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the ships in\Nthis area helped 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.30,0:08:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's the sailors' code to work\Ntogether when something happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.00,0:08:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that guy with\Nthe speedboat, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.03,0:08:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speedboat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.43,0:08:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it almost ran\Nstraight into my boat, here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.02,0:08:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably some rich guy who goes\Naround sailing with other rich guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.56,0:08:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of speedboat was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.11,0:08:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the speedboat\Nhe was talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:08:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\NDon't get on without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.85,0:09:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diving equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the kidnapper and\NTakei Naoko may still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.47,0:09:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was no accident;\Nthe kidnapper drove off on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.67,0:09:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a means of escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper broke\Nthe side window with a hammer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.69,0:09:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was placed\Nin the car in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,swam underwater\Nto the opposite shore,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.66,0:09:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and got into\Na waiting speedboat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit then escaped
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.66,0:09:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the police were focusing\Ntheir attention on the mini-van.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.34,0:09:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.51,0:09:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably to confuse\Nthe police into thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.52,0:10:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that both kidnapper\Nand the hostage had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There could be other reasons, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing I don't understand\Nis about the hostage, Takei Naoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her body hasn't turned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only found enough scuba\Ndiving equipment for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.99,0:10:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did the kidnapper\Nget her out of the sunken car?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was she never in it at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.42,0:10:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she was seen inside it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.13,0:10:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!\NDid you find anything out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the manager here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the boat's owner simply abandoned\Nit and it hasn't been used since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.89,0:10:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that man\Nmistook it for another boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.02,0:10:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.02,0:10:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do I prove this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.77,0:10:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The investigation is cancelled?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What for? What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me. He was\Nthe one who decided to cancel it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know why, myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.28,0:11:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rich people are stingy, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.34,0:11:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably regrets wasting\Nmoney on his dead daughter now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! She's not dead at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.92,0:11:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.72,0:11:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.35,0:11:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.93,0:11:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to believe\Nthat Naoko's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh. Kids can be\Nso pampered sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.02,0:11:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. It's obvious once you\Nthink about it with a cool head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given the circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.86,0:11:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,neither the hostage nor the\Nkidnapper can possibly be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.03,0:11:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by doing this, he's basically insulting\Nyour reputation as a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.96,0:11:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a point there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.42,0:11:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter-- Naoko-- is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.76,0:12:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no bringing her back now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you want, isn't it?!\NYour cancellation fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.60,0:12:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it and get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want your lousy money!\NYou can keep it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! That old fogy really\Nknows how to piss me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I just remembered...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promised to meet my friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.72,0:12:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.43,0:12:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bah. That spoiled\Nlittle kid has it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.02,0:12:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His attitude changed too quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.31,0:12:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.75,0:12:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mistake about it!\NThe kidnapper must've contacted him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you just going\Nto let Naoko-{\i1}chan {\i0}die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.47,0:13:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Takei!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.26,0:13:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't really gather\Nall the money this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she might be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't even\Nknow if she's alive or not--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.48,0:13:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Takei! Have a look for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in the picture\Nthe kidnapper sent us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the newspaper has yesterday's date!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.71,0:13:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.08,0:13:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko-{\i1}chan {\i0}believes with\Nall her heart that you'll save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:13:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Takei!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I gather the 500 million now and\Nthen lose it in another stupid mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.38,0:13:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my latest business\Ndeal will go up in smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.73,0:14:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you see?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money or Naoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}?\NWhich is more important?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.75,0:14:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.78,0:14:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if this deal falls through,\Nmy company will go--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.86,0:14:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--bankrupt. There's no question about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.74,0:14:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about the company?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.46,0:14:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't replace Naoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s life!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.69,0:14:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I built this company\Nwith my own two hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.63,0:14:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, by sucking the\Nlifeblood out of other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.97,0:14:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Corporate raiding is a\Nperfectly legitimate business!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weak people lose! And the losers\Nhave no one to blame but themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That damn old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.86,0:14:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you little!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.67,0:14:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking for the bathroom--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.82,0:14:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is private property, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.90,0:15:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't tell anyone\Nabout this, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the police found out, Naoko-{\i1}chan\N{\i0}would be killed for sure this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.87,0:15:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.21,0:15:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't afford to let him\Nleave here for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.82,0:15:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lock him in your room or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.72,0:15:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to endure it for a short while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.06,0:15:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the deal is over,\NI promise we'll let you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what did the\Nkidnapper tell you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.15,0:15:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Prepare 500 million yen by tomorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw what kind\Nof person Mr. Takei is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.74,0:15:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll get the money if Naoko-{\i1}san\N{\i0}is important to him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money is the only\Nthing important to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a younger brother named Masahito.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:15:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Had"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He died, four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.39,0:16:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.60,0:16:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was still about your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.19,0:16:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. Let me hold you for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.53,0:16:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring some dinner later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.76,0:16:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you\Ncan fool the kidnapper
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with these wads of cash\Nmade out of newspaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet. This is the only choice left!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.48,0:17:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.52,0:17:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody's actually\Nseen Takei Naoko's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.03,0:17:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her mouth was taped\Nand she had a blindfold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no way\Nto see her face clearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.82,0:17:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper was the only\Nperson ever inside the mini-van!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! One person played the role of two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.33,0:17:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody once doubted that it was Naoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.68,0:17:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not unreasonable;\Nshe was far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.15,0:17:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and everyone just assumed it was her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.97,0:18:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. There are policemen hiding here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper was completely\Naware of what the police were up to!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.77,0:18:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper was always\Nright by Takei-{\i1}san{\i0}, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.28,0:18:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The diving watch mark on her arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her tan line from wearing a wetsuit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then what she did that one time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An ear-unplugging technique\Nthat every diver knows about!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.63,0:18:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must've injured her ears\Nwhen she suddenly entered the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.88,0:18:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!\NIt's long past our agreed time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.81,0:18:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kidnapper is here.\NHas been for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.85,0:18:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, you idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.52,0:18:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made me sprain my ankle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.32,0:19:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to the pain\Nyou gave my family, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.78,0:19:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.04,0:19:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the remains of a company\Nthat you took hostile control over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You don't mean that you're--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.20,0:19:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.05,0:19:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the daughter of the\Nformer company director here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.13,0:19:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father killed himself,\Nand he took his wife and son with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.72,0:19:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving only me behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.41,0:19:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a college student at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.43,0:19:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was taken in by some\Nrelatives, changed my last name,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.27,0:19:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then joined your company.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To wait for a chance\Nto get revenge, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had loved Naoko-{\i1}chan\N{\i0}enough to simply get the money ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had intended to let you live!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.16,0:19:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:19:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.25,0:20:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gasoline?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I apologize!\NI'll pay as much as you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.35,0:20:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take your money with you to Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.57,0:20:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.58,0:20:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.16,0:20:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no value in killing that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no value in letting him live!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my duty to rid the world of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.63,0:20:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want Naoko-{\i1}san {\i0}to\Nthink the same way about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man is her only family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know more than anyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the pain of having\Nyour entire family die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:20:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you did get revenge, I don't\Nthink your brother would be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.74,0:21:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.17,0:21:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masahito...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:52.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just my imagination {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.70,0:22:02.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Playing with threads around my finger\Nwhile drinking lukewarm tea{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:11.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's walk lightly\Nto the bossa nova rhythm{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.51,0:22:16.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The puzzle pieces are in my hands{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:22.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:32.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was in the same place last week\Nbut with different clothes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.87,0:22:39.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Step by step,\Nthere's no reason to be anxious{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.88,0:22:46.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Case by case,\NI don't care if you laugh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:56.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond the countless days,\Nshe's waiting for me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.56,0:23:00.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta go my own way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.20,0:23:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takei Naoko was being held\Nin the basement of the old factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was rescued safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.62,0:23:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, she was\Nsomewhat aware of the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when she was first confined.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.42,0:23:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko! You're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.50,0:23:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.22,0:23:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry I got you\Ninvolved, Naoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.29,0:23:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.97,0:24:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still can't say anything for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.76,0:24:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he really attacked for no reason as she says,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.64,0:24:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then he'll probably\Nhave to be put to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.81,0:24:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come back, Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.13,0:24:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who can save John!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.42,0:24:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.04,0:24:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,John the Dog's Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.35,0:24:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.60,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reflex action to a situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:24:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is--John, dinnertime. Wait.
